; scene-features-organ.fk — scene-features re-expressed as a THIN sensor-organ over the high-grammar
; sensor-organ-template.fk. The structural spine (mint the afferent port, route the feature to its plane
; as a mesh-safe reading) now LIVES IN THE TEMPLATE; this file declares only what makes scene-features
; scene-features: its three contract ATTRIBUTES and its ONE feature recipe.
;
; THE DECLARED ATTRIBUTES (the so-organ data row):
;   NAME    "scene"          — the organ's id
;   PLANE   "what"           — scene-features answers the WHAT plane (what is in this place) — inquiry-planes.fk
;   CARRIER "camera"         — the OS-API port (the downsampled NxN luminance grid the camera carrier produces)
;
; THE ONE FEATURE RECIPE (the only genuinely-varying organ-specific code): sf-feature reads the raw grid
; into a single banded SCENE feature — the count of coarse blocks that hold a THING (object detail above
; the floor). This is the same MEAN-ABSOLUTE-DEVIATION block detail the original scene-features.fk proves
; (sf-detail over a 2x2 coarse block grid); the organ's banded "what" value is how many of the four
; coarse blocks read as objects. The richer per-block bands (sf-shape / sf-objects / sf-common?) stay the
; same recipes; the organ's routed feature is the scalar the mesh fuses on the "what" plane.
;
; EVERYTHING ELSE — the afferent port (so-port -> wsf-sensor "camera" "what"), the mesh-safe reading
; (so-route -> wsf-route -> fo-reading), the fusion (so-observe -> wsf-fuse) — is INHERITED from the
; template. scene-features no longer re-inlines wsf-sensor / wsf-route; it DECLARES and INHERITS.
;
; preludes: form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/spatial-fusion.fk form-stdlib/confidence-weighted-vote.fk form-stdlib/mesh-sense-7w.fk form-stdlib/fused-observation.fk form-stdlib/world-sensor-floor.fk form-stdlib/sensor-organ-template.fk
;
; Proven by: observe/tests/src-witness/scene-features-organ-witness.fk (fkwu --src — SAME verdict as the
;            original scene-features feature math), and observe/tests/sensor-organ-template-band.fk.

(do
    ; ── the ORGAN: scene-features' three contract attributes, declared over the template. ──
    (defn scene-organ () (so-organ "scene" "what" "camera"))

    ; ── the "what" feature REUSES the original scene-features recipe (sf-objects) verbatim — the organ
    ;    inherits the route+fuse spine from the template, and inherits the FEATURE math from the sensor it
    ;    re-expresses. This is what makes the uplift byte-identical: the one varying recipe is the proven
    ;    one, not a re-implementation. A SAMPLE is (grid n detail-floor) — the carrier's downsampled
    ;    luminance grid, its size, and the object detail floor. The banded "what" value is how many coarse
    ;    blocks hold a THING (the length of the original sf-objects inventory). ──
    (defn sf-feature (sample)
        (len (sf-objects (nth sample 0) (nth sample 1) (nth sample 2))))

    ; ── INHERIT the route spine from the template: the reading is so-route over the organ + the feature-fn.
    ;    No wsf-sensor / wsf-route re-inlined here — the template carries it. ──
    (defn scene-route (sample confidence) (so-route (scene-organ) sf-feature sample confidence))

    0)
